&gt; &gt; &gt; I took a look.  Apart from the two JS-set cookies, TEST_P, and
&gt; &gt; TEST_S,
&gt; &gt; &gt; there are other interesting issues around WP login.
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; The expiry date sent over by the washington post is beginning of
&gt; &gt; the
&gt; &gt; &gt; epoch.  The httpclient lib that underpins heritrix is choosing to
&gt; &gt; treat
&gt; &gt; &gt; cookies marked with this expiration date as &#39;expired&#39; which seems
&gt; &gt; proper.
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Here are the set-cookie headers sent by the WP login page:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; 1. Set-Cookie: TEST_P=; domain=.washingtonpost.com;
&gt; &gt; expires=Thursday,
&gt; &gt; &gt; 01-Jan-1970 01:00:00 GMT; path=/
&gt; &gt; &gt; 2. Set-Cookie: TEST_S=; domain=.washingtonpost.com;
&gt; &gt; expires=Thursday,
&gt; &gt; &gt; 01-Jan-1970 01:00:00 GMT; path=/
&gt; &gt; &gt; 3. Set-Cookie:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; UPROF=WU9CPTE5NjArRz1tYWxlK1pJUD05NDExNytVVD1leHBsaWNpdCtDPVVuaXRlZCBTdGF0ZXMrQj1QUk9GRVMrQj1FTkdOK0I9U09GVERFVitCPVNJWkVfMQ==;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; domain=.washingtonpost.com; expires=Thursday, 01-Jan-1970 01:00:00
&gt; &gt; GMT;
&gt; &gt; &gt; path=/
&gt; &gt; &gt; 4. Set-Cookie: UPDATED=1101314587; domain=.washingtonpost.com;
&gt; &gt; &gt; expires=Thursday, 01-Jan-1970 01:00:00 GMT; path=/
&gt; &gt; &gt; 5. Set-Cookie: wpniuser=stack@d...; domain=.washingtonpost.com;
&gt; &gt; &gt; expires=Thursday, 01-Jan-1970 01:00:00 GMT; path=/
&gt; &gt; &gt; NODATE,NODOMAIN BUT GETS RETURNED BY CRAWLER+++Set-Cookie:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; WebLogicSessionAc2=Bk6bKOkXvrj1aj0sF81Sd2RCmzF4j1B7g3t1ni1qSzcL3fdLrNd5!1390141459!-763422351;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; path=/+Set-Cookie:
&gt; &gt; &gt; WPATC=A=1:D=3:C=2:E=JEBBH:S=8:S=245:B=7:B=29:B=78:B=100:VS=3;
&gt; &gt; &gt; domain=.washingtonpost.com; path=/
&gt; &gt; &gt; 6. Set-Cookie:
&gt; &gt; &gt; WPATC=A=1:D=3:C=2:E=JEBBH:S=8:S=245:B=7:B=29:B=78:B=100:VS=3;
&gt; &gt; &gt; domain=.washingtonpost.com; expires=Saturday, 26-Jan-2008 02:29:46
&gt; &gt; GMT;
&gt; &gt; &gt; path=/
&gt; &gt; &gt; 7. Set-Cookie: SESSIONREM=stack@d...; domain=.washingtonpost.com;
&gt; &gt; &gt; path=/
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Here is what the browser sends back when it goes against the
&gt; &gt; &gt; washingtonpost.com domain:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Cookie:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; UPROF=WU9CPTE5NjArRz1tYWxlK1pJUD05NDExNytVVD1leHBsaWNpdCtDPVVuaXRlZCBTdGF0ZXMrQj1QUk9GRVMrQj1FTkdOK0I9U09GVERFVitCPVNJWkVfMQ==;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; UPDATED=1101314409; SESSIONREM=stack@d...;
&gt; &gt; &gt; wpniuser=stack@d...;
&gt; &gt; &gt; WPATC=A=1:D=3:C=2:E=JEBBH:S=8:S=245:B=7:B=29:B=78:B=100:VS=3
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Here is what Heritrix sends back if its under the &#39;/ac&#39; path:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Cookie: SESSIONREM=stack@d...;
&gt; &gt; &gt; WPATC=A=1:D=3:C=2:E=JEBBH:S=8:S=245:B=7:B=29:B=78:B=100:VS=3
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Heritrix is missing the &#39;UPROF&#39;, &#39;UPDATED&#39;, and &#39;wpniuser&#39; cookie
&gt; &gt; &gt; elements (Items 3., 4., and 5. above).  Notice that the expiration
&gt; &gt; date
&gt; &gt; &gt; set on these cookie elements is &#39;Thursday, 01-Jan-1970 01:00:00
&gt; &gt; GMT&#39;. 
&gt; &gt; &gt; Browsers seem to return cookies marked with this date as unexpired.
&gt; &gt;  The
&gt; &gt; &gt; httpclient lib passes them over.
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; There&#39;s a configuration on the heritrix CookiePolicy to say whether
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; cookie policy should be strict or browser compatible.   Heritrix
&gt; &gt; has it
&gt; &gt; &gt; set to browser compatible but looks like 1970 is a special date as
&gt; &gt; far
&gt; &gt; &gt; as browsers are concerned (Looking in httpclient lib source, there
&gt; &gt; is no
&gt; &gt; &gt; special handling for the 1970 date that I can see).  Anyone know
&gt; &gt; &gt; anything about this?  Otherwise, time to look in browser src.
